content.description: Start on Lessa (first route of Dead Cats) and move up to the part of the wall about 2/3rds of the way up with juggy holds and move left.   It crosses over all the routes on Rhetorick Wall. You clip the bolts above this band of jug filled rock on each route you cross.  Eventually you end up on Talk it Up where you head upwards to the anchors.  Belay TR from anchors from Talk it Up.
content.location: Starts on Lessa the Puramatic 6000 Kitty, the 1st route of Dead Cats Wall, and transverses the entire Rhetorick Wall ending up at the anchors for Talk it Up.

content.description: Starts on a chossy face. As it gets steeper there's a ledge on the left, then a huge Texas-shaped flake left of the boltline and left of the anchors.
Start on Twyman's Folly (Quest for Zest), bypass the drilled pocket, and cut left at the steep setion onto Schizophrenic Calisthenics.
content.location: Start on Quest for Zest.  Finish on Schizophrenic Calisthenics.  Rhetorick Wall, Reimer's Ranch.

content.description: Move up towards a dihedral from the ledge of Rhetorick Wall to the right of Talk it Up.  Instead of veering off to the left, as in Choss it Up, you move up and to the right towards the orange streak and onto juggy holds and a hueco.  At the top of the orange streak you move to the left and then up using a wide variety of interesting moves.  Definitely a great and accurate name!  Schizophrenic Calisthenics!
content.protection: Two bolts, sport anchors at the top
content.location: Rhetorick Wall, right of Talk it up and left of Quest for Zest

content.description:
Sequence rich face climbing leads to a mini nose. Crux is pulling over this bulge. Hard moves on plenty of holds provide plenty of options. Juggy finish makes anchor clipping safe and satisfying. 

  Moves are possible for climbers of any height. We talked to a local guy who said a buddy of his (5' 2") can pull it.
content.location: Wall is to the left of DeadCats in a small stepped down area. Counting from "Talk it Up" which is the left most route, "Rhetoric" is the forth route to the right and one left of "Punctuation Mark (12a) ". Look for the orange mini cave just below a bulge with two large jugs inside.

content.description: Originally called Twyman's Folly.  Starts on the small dihedral at a diagonal down-facing thin crack.  Starts to the left of Rhetorick.  Climbs up and to two bolts and anchors.
content.location: To the left of Rhetorick and to the right of Schizophrenic Calisthenics

content.description: Follows a line of slopey holds that get more desperate toward the top. Bottom part will be easier for taller climbers - top may be easier for shorter. Clipping holds are safe. Watch out for cacti.
content.protection: 3 bolts on face. 2 large old-school bolts for anchors at top.
content.location: Right of Rhetoric. Left of super easy 5.6 that all the guided groups climb.

content.description: Start on Schizophrenic Calisthenics and arc your way towards the Talk it up anchors. You will begin traversing over the mini dihedral and mini roof towards anchors.
content.location: Left side of Rhetorick wall. Start Schizophrenic route and angle towards Talk it up anchors. You will need to lead Talk it up first.

content.description: This wall is a continuation of Dead Cats past Mario's Route. Routes listed from right to left.
